    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Bring Back the Borders! 1.1.0]]></title>
        <id>https://windhawk.net/mods/w11-dwm-fix#c267265e0049c3f7feb015e3ec2e6f5d6b7bc483</id>
        <link href="https://windhawk.net/mods/w11-dwm-fix"/>
        <updated>2024-02-10T19:18:31.000Z</updated>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="bringbacktheborders">Bring back the borders!</h1>
<p>A simple mod to restore borders and corners in Windows 11.</p>
<p>Based on the
<a href="https://windhawk.net/mods/disable-rounded-corners">Disable rounded corners in Windows 11</a>
project by m417z.</p>
<p>Based on the
<a href="https://github.com/valinet/Win11DisableRoundedCorners">Win11DisableRoundedCorners</a>
project by Valentin Radu.</p>
<h2 id="importantusagenote">⚠ Important usage note ⚠</h2>
<p>In order to use this mod, you must allow Windhawk to inject into the <strong>dwm.exe</strong>
system process. To do so, add it to the process inclusion list in the advanced
settings. If you do not do this, it will silently fail to inject.</p>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/LRhREtJ.png" alt="Advanced settings screenshot" /></p>]]></content>
